write_metric(25.10)                                        write_metric(25.10)

Name write_metric - Writes the current set of metrics to a file or stdout
Syntax
Parameters  -format  <output_format>  Specifies  the output format, json, xml,
       csv, tcl. Default: JSON Data_type: string,  optional  -help  Outputs  a
       brief  description  that includes type and default information for each
       write_metric parameter. For a detailed description of the  command  and
       all  of its parameters, use the man command: man write_metric <-id met-
       ric_id > Specifies a list of labels from read_metrics. Default: Current
       metric Data_type: string, optional -merge Merges the  results  into  an
       existing  file.  Data_type:  bool,  optional -names  <list_of_patterns>
       Specifies the list of patterns  to  match  snapshot  names.  Data_type:
       string, optional <pattern> List of regular expressions to chose metrics
       to  write.  Default  is  all  metrics  (*). Data_type: string, optional
       -out_file <fileName> Specifies the name of the file in which metrics is
       written. Data_type: string, optional
Example
